{%- comment -%}
  Site-wide news ticker. Pulls the 5 most recent items from
  _news/, sorted by `date` descending. The whole strip is one
  anchor → /news/ for clean a11y. "LATEST NEWS" label on the
  left and "All news →" link on the right stay static; the
  middle area is a horizontal marquee scrolling right-to-left
  via CSS keyframes (see _sass/_tmslab.scss section for
  `.tmslab-ticker-scroll-*` rules).

  Content is duplicated once in the track so the scroll loops
  seamlessly — when the first pass leaves on the left, the
  duplicate enters the visible area, and the CSS -100%
  translate wraps back to 0 invisibly.

  One-line summaries: each item's body is run through
    markdownify | strip_html | strip_newlines | strip
  so markdown links become plain text and HTML tags/comments
  are removed.

  Rotation logic was removed from /assets/js/news-ticker.js —
  the animation is now pure CSS. The JS file just handles
  reduced-motion a11y + optional dynamic duration.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign recent_news = site.news | sort: "date" | reverse -%}
{%- assign news_count = recent_news | size -%}

{%- if news_count > 0 -%}
<a href="{{ '/news/' | relative_url }}" class="tmslab-ticker" aria-label="Latest lab news; opens the news page">
  <div class="tmslab-ticker-inner">
    <span class="tmslab-ticker-prefix">Latest news</span>

    <div class="tmslab-ticker-scroll-viewport" aria-label="Scrolling news headlines">
      <div class="tmslab-ticker-scroll-track">
        {%- for item in recent_news limit: 5 -%}
          {%- capture clean -%}{{ item.content | markdownify | strip_html | strip_newlines | strip }}{%- endcapture -%}
          <span>{{ clean | truncate: 200 }}</span>
        {%- endfor -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Duplicated set for seamless loop — as the first pass
          scrolls off-left, the duplicate is entering from the
          right, so there's never a visible gap or "jump back".
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- for item in recent_news limit: 5 -%}
          {%- capture clean -%}{{ item.content | markdownify | strip_html | strip_newlines | strip }}{%- endcapture -%}
          <span aria-hidden="true">{{ clean | truncate: 200 }}</span>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>
    </div>

    <span class="tmslab-ticker-link" aria-hidden="true">All news →</span>
  </div>
</a>
<script src="{{ '/assets/js/news-ticker.js' | relative_url }}" defer></script>
{%- endif -%}
